			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: I need twisting explained<a name="29649"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 23 04 9:54 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The guide section will certainly explain it in detail but let me throw out some information to get you started.
<br />

<br />
Sounds like you understand the basics of twisting already the problem is with song duration.  What bards actually do though is to pick anywhere from 2+ song (I generally twist either 3 or 4 depending on what is needed) and sing them in rotation.  Let's use a 3 song twist as an example.  You start singing the first one and the instant the song takes effect, you sing the next one in line.  When the second takes effect, you sing the third.  As soon as the third song takes effect, you re-sing song number 1.  By doing that you are constantly cycling through the 3 songs and all 3 song effects are on you or your group at all times.  
<br />

<br />
The vast majority of songs are a 3 tick duration and have a 3 second cast time.  So for regular use you'll likely only be twisting 3 or 4 songs at a time reliably.  There are tricks to twisting more but I haven't delved into that yet.  Hope this helps a bit.  Oh, and get used to talking less in game while twisting.  Lol.  </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">Bardtail Mathers
Lvl 65 Maestro of Stromm
Fellowship Of The Dragonlords</span></td>
